  "prompt": "What\u2019s the industry average commission for a forex trader?",
  "response": "In the forex trading industry, commission rates can vary widely depending on the broker, account type, and trading volume. However, here are some general guidelines:\n\n1. Spread-based pricing (most common):\n- Average spreads range from 0.5 to 3 pips\n- Some brokers offer as low as 0.0 pips for certain account types\n\n2. Commission-based pricing:\n- Typically $2-$7 per standard lot (100,000 units)\n- Commission rates can be lower for high-volume traders\n\n3. Hybrid pricing:\n- Combination of spread and commission\n- Often ranges from $3-$5 per lot plus tight spreads\n\nExact rates depend on factors like:\n- Broker type (ECN, market maker, etc.)\n- Trading platform\n- Account size\n- Trading frequency\n- Currency pairs traded\n\nIt's recommended to compare multiple brokers and their specific fee structures to find the most suitable option for your trading style and volume.",
